to
listen.”
He
took
her
hand.
“I
am
your
brother,
you
know.
You
need
me,
whether
you
care
to
admit
it
or
no.
Your
son
needs
me,
if
he’s
to
have
a
hope
of
retaining
that
ugly
iron
chair.”

His
sister
seemed
shocked
that
he
would
touch
her.
“You
have
always
been
cunning.”

“In
my
own
small
way.”
He
grinned.

“It
may
be
worth
the
trying…
but
make
no
mistake,
Tyrion.
If
I
accept
you,
you
shall
be
the
King’s
Hand
in
name,
but
my
Hand
in
truth.
You
will
share
all
your
plans
and
