“That
one
belongs
to
the
Hound’s
brother,”
Sansa
had
confided
when
they
passed
the
black
dogs
on
the
yellow
field.
“He’s
even
bigger
than
Hodor,
you’ll
see.
They
call
him
the
Mountain
That
Rides.”

Arya
let
her
head
droop,
only
half
aware
of
what
was
going
on
around
her.
Hot
Pie
was
yielding
some
more.
The
Mountain
said,
“You’ll
lead
us
to
these
others,”
and
walked
off.
Next
she
was
stumbling
past
the
dead
men
on
their
