Bronn
warned.

“Good.
The
longer
Cersei
waits,
the
angrier
she’ll
become,
and
anger
makes
her
stupid.
I
much
prefer
angry
and
stupid
to
composed
and
cunning.”
Tyrion
tossed
his
folded
cloak
into
his
litter,
and
Timett
helped
him
up
after
it.

The
market
square
inside
the
Gate
of
the
Gods,
which
in
normal
times
would
have
been
thronged
with
farmers
selling
vegetables,
was
near
deserted
when
Tyrion
crossed
it.
Ser
Jacelyn
met
him
at
the
gate,
and
raised
his
iron
hand
in
