“Wine
for
the
King’s
Hand,”
he
told
the
girl,
gesturing
Ned
to
a
couch.
“I
am
Tobho
Mott,
my
lord,
please,
please,
put
yourself
at
ease.”
He
wore
a
black
velvet
coat
with
hammers
embroidered
on
the
sleeves
in
silver
thread,
Around
his
neck
was
a
heavy
