stone
pillow.
“Dunsen,
Polliver,
Chiswyck,
Raff
the
Sweetling.
The
Tickler
and
the
Hound.
Ser
Amory,
Ser
Ilyn,
Ser
Meryn,
King
Joffrey,
Queen
Cersei.”
Back
in
Winterfell,
Arya
had
prayed
with
her
mother
in
the
sept
and
with
her
father
in
the
godswood,
but
there
were
no
gods
on
the
road
to
Harrenhal,
and
her
names
were
the
only
prayer
she
cared
to
remember.

Every
day
they
marched,
and
every
night
she
said
her
names,
until
finally
the
trees
thinned
and
gave
way
to
