They
read
their
crumbling
scrolls,
drink
shade-of-the-evening
until
their
lips
turn
blue,
and
hint
of
dread
powers,
but
they
are
hollow
husks
compared
to
those
who
went
before.
Pyat
Pree’s
gifts
will
turn
to
dust
in
your
hands,
I
warn
you.”
He
gave
his
camel
a
lick
of
