of
the
Seven
Kingdoms
half
a
world
away.
“You
would
do
well
to
avoid
both
those
men,
Your
Grace.”

“Those
men
will
help
me
to
my
crown,”
she
said.
“Xaro
has
vast
wealth,
and
Pyat
Pree—”

“—pretends
to
power,”
the
knight
said
brusquely.
On
his
dark
green
surcoat,
the
bear
of
House
Mormont
stood
on
its
hind
legs,
black
and
fierce.
Jorah
looked
no
less
ferocious
as
he
scowled
at
the
crowd
that
filled
the
bazaar.
“I
would
not
linger
here
long,
my
queen.
I
mislike
the
very
smell
of
this
place.”

Dany
smiled.
“Perhaps
it’s
the
camels
you’re
smelling.
The
Qartheen
themselves
seem
sweet
enough
to
my
nose.”

“Sweet
smells
are
sometimes
used
to
cover
foul
ones.”

My
great
bear,
Dany
thought.
I
am
his
queen,
but
I
will
always
be
his
cub
as
well,
and
he
will
always
guard
me.
It
made
her
feel
safe,
but
sad
as
