He
protects
no
man,
I
promise
you.
He
is
the
enemy
of
all
that
lives.
It
is
the
torches
that
hide
us,
you
have
said
so
yourself.
Fire.
The
bright
gift
of
the
Lord
of
Light.”

“Have
it
your
way.”

“His
way,
rather.”

The
wind
was
shifting,
Davos
could
feel
it,
see
it
in
the
way
the
black
canvas
rippled.
He
reached
for
the
halyards.
“Help
me
bring
in
the
sail.
I’ll
row
us
the
rest
