her.
Two
arms
wriggled
free,
grasping,
black
fingers
coiling
around
Melisandre’s
straining
thighs,
pushing,
until
the
whole
of
the
shadow
slid
out
into
the
world
and
rose
taller
than
Davos,
tall
as
the
tunnel,
towering
above
the
boat.
He
had
only
an
instant
to
look
at
it
before
it
was
gone,
twisting
between
the
bars
of
the
portcullis
and
racing
across
the
surface
of
the
water,
but
that
instant
was
long
enough.

He
knew
that
shadow.
As
he
knew
the
man
who’d
cast
it.
=======
queen.

“Pycelle
swears
it
will
heal
clean.”
Robert
frowned.
“I
take
it
you
know
what
Catelyn
has
done?”

“I
do.”
Ned
took
a
small
swallow
of
wine.
“My
lady
wife
is
blameless,
Your
Grace.
All
she
did
she
did
at
my
command.”

“I
am
not
