“Damn
him!”
Tyrion
said.

Varys
smiled,
showing
a
mouth
full
of
rotted
teeth.
“Who,
my
lord?
Ser
Cortnay
or
Lord
Stannis?”

“Both
of
them.”
Storm’s
End
was
strong,
it
should
have
been
able
to
hold
out
for
half
a
year
or
more…
time
enough
for
his
father
to
finish
with
Robb
Stark.
“How
did
this
happen?”

Varys
glanced
at
Shae.
“My
lord,
must
we
trouble
your
sweet
lady’s
sleep
with
such
grim
and
bloody
talk?”

“A
lady
might
be
afraid,”
said
Shae,
“but
I’m
not.”

“You
should
be,”
Tyrion
told
her.
“With
Storm’s
End
fallen,
Stannis
will
soon
turn
his
attention
toward
King’s
Landing.”
He
regretted
flinging
away
that
wine
now.
“Lord
Varys,
give
us
a
moment,
and
I’ll
ride
back
to
the
castle
with
