“So
soon?”
she
said,
confused.
“I’ve
walked
for
hours,
and
still
not
found
them.”

“You
have
taken
a
wrong
turning.
Come,
I
will
lead
you.”
Pyat
Pree
held
out
his
hand.

Dany
hesitated.
There
was
a
door
to
her
right,
still
closed…

“That’s
not
the
way,”
Pyat
Pree
said
firmly,
his
blue
lips
prim
with
disapproval.
“The
Undying
Ones
will
not
wait
forever.”

“Our
little
lives
are
no
more
than
a
flicker
of
a
moth’s
