to
them,”
Dany
said,
remembering.

“Stubborn
child.
You
will
be
lost,
and
never
found.”

She
walked
away
from
him,
to
the
door
on
the
right.

“No,”
Pyat
screeched.
“No,
to
me,
come
to
me,
to
meeeeeee.”
His
face
crumbled
inward,
changing
to
something
pale
and
