“I
was
the
youngest
man
ever
to
wear
the
white
cloak.”

“And
the
youngest
to
betray
all
it
stood
for,
Kingslayer.”

“Kingslayer,”
he
pronounced
carefully.
“And
such
a
king
he
was!”
He
lifted
his
cup.
“To
Aerys
Targaryen,
the
Second
of
His
Name,
Lord
of
the
Seven
Kingdoms
and
Protector
of
the
Realm.
And
to
the
sword
that
opened
his
throat.
A
golden
sword,
don’t
you
know.
Until
his
blood
ran
red
down
the
blade.
Those
are
the
Lannister
colors,
red
and
gold.”

As
