“Is
it
safe,
my
lord?”
Qyburn
asked.
“Only
three
days
past,
Septon
Utt’s
men
were
attacked
by
wolves.
They
came
right
into
his
camp,
not
five
yards
from
the
fire,
and
killed
two
horses.”

“It
is
wolves
I
mean
to
hunt.
I
can
scarcely
sleep
at
night
for
the
howling.”
Bolton
buckled
on
his
belt,
adjusting
the
hang
of
sword
and
