flying.
“The
Tickler,”
she
called
out
one
time,
“the
Hound,”
the
next.
“Ser
Ilyn,
Ser
Meryn,
Queen
Cersei.”
The
bole
of
an
oak
loomed
before
her,
and
she
lunged
to
drive
her
point
through
