grunting
“Joffrey,
Joffrey,
Joffrey.”
Her
arms
and
legs
were
dappled
by
sunlight
and
the
shadows
of
leaves.
A
sheen
of
sweat
covered
her
skin
by
the
time
she
paused.
The
heel
of
her
right
foot
was
bloody
where
she’d
skinned
it,
so
she
stood
one-legged
