and
the
yellow
pages
stirred
as
they
burned,
as
if
some
ghost
were
reading
them.
“I
will
have
no
further
need
of
you
tonight,”
he
said,
never
looking
at
her.

She
should
have
gone,
silent
as
a
mouse,
but
something
had
hold
of
her.
“My
lord,”
she
asked,
“will
you
take
me
with
you
when
you
leave
Harrenhal?”

He
turned
to
stare
at
her,
and
from
the
look
in
his
