it
was
as
if
his
supper
had
just
spoken
to
him.
“Did
I
give
you
leave
to
question
me,
Nan?”

“No,
my
lord.”
She
lowered
her
eyes.

“You
should
not
have
spoken,
then.
Should
you?”

“No.
My
lord.”

For
a
moment
he
looked
amused.
“I
will
answer
you,
just
this
once.
I
mean
to
give
Harrenhal
to
Lord
Vargo
when
I
return
to
the
north.
You
will
remain
here,
with
