they
each
chewed
a
half-frozen
strip
of
horsemeat,
then
saddled
their
garrons
once
again,
and
fastened
their
black
cloaks
around
their
shoulders.
During
his
watch
the
Halfhand
had
made
a
half-dozen
torches,
soaking
