of
dry
moss
with
the
oil
he
carried
in
his
saddlebag.
He
lit
the
first
one
now
and
led
the
way
down
into
the
dark,
holding
the
pale
flame
up
before
him.
Jon
followed
with
the
horses.
The
stony
path
twisted
and
turned,
first
down,
then
up,
then
down
more
