In
spots
it
grew
so
narrow
it
was
hard
to
convince
the
garrons
they
could
squeeze
through.
By
the
time
we
come
out
we
will
have
lost
them,
he
told
himself
as
they
went.
Not
even
an
eagle
can
see
through
solid
stone.
We
will
have
lost
them,
and
we
will
ride
hard
for
the
Fist,
and
tell
the
Old
Bear
all
we
know.

But
when
they
emerged
back
into
the
light
long
