Pyp
spurred
his
horse
closer,
reciting,
“I
am
the
fire
that
burns
against
the
cold,
the
light
that
brings
the
dawn,
the
horn
that
wakes
the
sleepers,
>>>>>>> asd
the
shield
that
guards
the
realms
of
<<<<<<< 1441d55ef0d8b5e242e34427404d9d5041159095
men.

A
hunting
horn
echoed
through
the
mountains,
and
a
moment
later
Jon
heard
the
baying
of
hounds.
“They
will
be
with
us
soon,”
announced
Qhorin.
“Keep
your
wolf
in
hand.”

“Ghost,
to
me,”
Jon
called.
The
direwolf
returned
reluctantly
to
his
side,
tail
held
stiffly
behind
him.

The
wildlings
came
boiling
over
a
ridge
not
half
a
mile
away.
Their
hounds
ran
before
them,
snarling
grey-brown
beasts
with
more
than
a
little
wolf
in
