“Stay.”
Overhead
he
heard
a
rustle
of
wings.
The
eagle
landed
on
an
outcrop
of
rock
and
screamed
in
triumph.

The
hunters
approached
warily,
perhaps
fearing
arrows.
Jon
counted
fourteen,
with
eight
dogs.
Their
large
round
shields
were
made
of
skins
stretched
over
woven
