Qhorin
snorted.
“I
see
no
lord.
Only
a
dog
dressed
in
chickenbones,
who
rattles
when
he
rides.”

The
wildling
hissed
in
anger,
and
his
mount
reared.
He
did
rattle,
Jon
could
hear
it;
the
bones
were
strung
together
loosely,
so
they
clacked
and
clattered
when
he
moved.
“It’s
your
bones
I’ll
be
rattling
soon,
Halfhand.
I’ll
boil
the
flesh
off
you
and
make
a
byrnie
from
your
ribs.
I’ll
carve
your
teeth
to
cast
me
