and
eat
me
oaten
porridge
from
your
skull.”

“If
you
want
my
bones,
come
get
them.”

That,
Rattleshirt
seemed
reluctant
to
do.
His
numbers
meant
little
in
the
close
confines
of
the
rocks
where
the
black
brothers
had
taken
their
stand;
to
winkle
them
out
