yet
you
don’t
see
me
running
off.
I
said
the
words,
just
as
you
did.
My
place
is
here…
where
is
yours,
boy?”

I
have
no
place,
Jon
wanted
to
say,
I’m
a
bastard,
I
have
no
rights,
no
name,
no
mother,
and
now
not
even
a
father.
The
words
would
not
come.
“I
don’t
know.”

“I
do,”
said
Lord
Commander
Mormont.
“The
cold
winds
are
rising,
Snow.
Beyond
the
Wall,
the
shadows
lengthen.
Cotter
Pyke
writes
of
vast
herds
of
elk,
streaming
south
