“Ben
Jen,”
the
raven
squawked,
bobbing
its
head,
bits
of
egg
dribbling
from
its
beak.
“Ben
Jen.
Ben
Jen.”

“No,”
Jon
said.
There
had
been
others.
Too
many.

“Do
you
think
your
brother’s
war
is
more
important
than
ours?”
the
old
man
barked.

Jon
chewed
his
lip.
The
raven
flapped
its
wings
at
him.
“War,
war,
war,
war,”
it
sang.

“It’s
not,”
Mormont
told
him.
“Gods
save
