who
sits
the
Iron
Throne?”

“No.”
Jon
had
not
thought
of
it
that
way.

“Your
lord
father
sent
you
to
us,
Jon.
Why,
who
can
say?”

“Why?
Why?
Why?”
the
raven
called.

“All
I
know
is
that
the
blood
of
the
First
Men
flows
in
the
veins
of
the
Starks.
The
First
Men
built
the
Wall,
and
it’s
said
they
remember
things
otherwise
forgotten.
And
that
beast
of
yours…
he
led
us
to
the
wights,
warned
you
of
the
dead
man
on
the
steps.
Ser
Jaremy
would
doubtless
call
that
happenstance,
yet
Ser
Jaremy
is
